Recent News



MarketWatch
Other Dow Jones










Royal Bank of Canada's earnings top estimates
Royal Bank of Canada's sales and profit handily topped expectations in the second quarter, led by gains in its fee-based businesses. Net interest income increased 4.2% to 4.2 billion Canadian dollars while noninterest income climbed 11% to C$6.11 billion. Toronto-based RBC, Canada's largest lender by assets, said its net profit jumped to C$2.81 billion, or C$1.85 a share, in its latest quarter ending April 30, from C$2.57 billion, or C$1.66 a share, a year earlier.

May. 25, 2017 at 1:57 p.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com









Royal Bank of Canada's earnings top estimates
Royal Bank of Canada's sales and profit handily topped expectations in the first quarter, led by gains in fee-based businesses. Net interest income increased 4.2% to 4.2 billion Canadian dollars while noninterest income climbed 11% to C$6.11 billion. Toronto-based RBC, Canada's largest lender by assets, said its net profit jumped to C$2.81 billion, or C$1.85 a share, in its latest quarter ending April 30, from C$2.57 billion, or C$1.66 a share, a year earlier.

